    "3) Application in genetic diseases: The strategy of correcting point mutations associated with genetic diseases while preserving genetic function is one of the ideal ways to treat genetic diseases.",
    "In 2014, Yin et al.",
    "reported a study of CRISPR/ Cas9-mediated HDR correction of Fah gene point mutations in adult mice, demonstrating that correcting gene mutations using CRISPR/ Cas9-mediated gene editing is feasible in adult animals and has the potential to correct genetic mutations for human genetic diseases.",
    "This strategy has also been applied to the study of other similar genetic diseases.",
    "For example, Yang et al."
